description.en:
The metropolis of Hasgar is crossed by an imposing wall. On the west side, there is a huge ghetto, where terrorism and misery wreak havoc. On the East side, in the city center are standing up high ultramodern towers, where the rich and the leaders live.

In the chaos of the poor neighborhood, a new hero appears. Armed with a metal bar, his face hidden under a gas mask, his ears covered with a helmet spitting music, he comes out of nowhere when despair is at its height and crushes his enemies in an unleashead violence. He's called&hellip; Guess What!

The governor, who cannot leave such a disturbing element in the city, calls on Nika, an elite soldier, to investigate. But as seasoned as she is, the young woman is far from imagining the terrifying secrets buried in the shallows of Hasgar&hellip;
